### TOOL 1.1: Contractor Hourly Rate Calculator

**Target Search:** "how much should I charge as a handyman", "contractor hourly rate calculator"

**URL:** /tools/hourly-rate-calculator

**Description:** Helps contractors calculate what hourly rate they need to charge to hit their income goals after expenses.

**Inputs:**
| Field | Type | Validation | Default |
|-------|------|------------|---------|
| Desired Annual Income | currency | min: 0, max: 500000 | 75000 |
| Annual Business Expenses | currency | min: 0 | 15000 |
| Annual Vehicle Costs | currency | min: 0 | 8000 |
| Annual Tool/Equipment Costs | currency | min: 0 | 3000 |
| Annual Insurance Costs | currency | min: 0 | 4000 |
| Estimated Tax Rate | percentage | 0-50 | 25 |
| Billable Hours Per Week | number | 1-80 | 30 |
| Weeks Worked Per Year | number | 1-52 | 48 |

**Calculation Logic:**
```
totalExpenses = businessExpenses + vehicleCosts + toolCosts + insuranceCosts
grossNeeded = (desiredIncome + totalExpenses) / (1 - taxRate/100)
totalBillableHours = billableHoursPerWeek * weeksWorkedPerYear
hourlyRate = grossNeeded / totalBillableHours
```

**Outputs:**
- Recommended Hourly Rate (prominent display)
- Breakdown: Gross revenue needed, tax set-aside, take-home after expenses
- Comparison: "If you charge $X/hour, you'd make $Y/year"

**UI Components:**
- Slider inputs for quick adjustment
- Real-time calculation (no submit button)
- Results card with animated number transitions
- "Save My Rate" button (stores to localStorage)
- Share results button
- Print/PDF export

**CTA:** "Track every job and know your real hourly earnings with C-Money →"

**SEO Metadata:**
```
title: "Contractor Hourly Rate Calculator | Free Tool | C-Money"
description: "Calculate exactly what hourly rate you need to charge as a contractor to hit your income goals. Free calculator for handymen, electricians, plumbers, and more."
keywords: "contractor hourly rate, handyman pricing calculator, how much to charge per hour, trade business calculator"
```

**Tests:**
- [ ] Unit test: Calculation accuracy with known inputs
- [ ] Edge case: Zero billable hours (should show error)
- [ ] Edge case: 100% tax rate (should cap or warn)
- [ ] UI test: All sliders update results in real-time
- [ ] Mobile test: Inputs usable on small screens
- [ ] A11y test: Screen reader announces results

