### TOOL 1.7: Materials Cost Estimator (Painting)

**Target Search:** "painting estimate calculator", "how much paint do I need"

**URL:** /tools/paint-calculator

**Description:** Estimate paint needed and cost based on room/area dimensions.

**Inputs:**
| Field | Type | Validation | Default |
|-------|------|------------|---------|
| Calculation Type | toggle | room OR total_sqft | room |
| Room Length (ft) | number | min: 1 | 12 |
| Room Width (ft) | number | min: 1 | 10 |
| Ceiling Height (ft) | number | min: 6, max: 20 | 8 |
| Number of Doors | number | min: 0 | 1 |
| Number of Windows | number | min: 0 | 2 |
| Total Wall Sq Ft (if not room) | number | min: 1 | 400 |
| Number of Coats | select | 1, 2, 3 | 2 |
| Paint Quality | select | economy, standard, premium | standard |
| Include Ceiling | boolean | | false |
| Include Trim | boolean | | false |

**Calculation Logic:**
```
// Wall area for room
wallArea = 2 * (length + width) * height
doorArea = numDoors * 21  // avg door is 3x7 = 21 sqft
windowArea = numWindows * 15  // avg window is ~15 sqft
paintableWallArea = wallArea - doorArea - windowArea

ceilingArea = includeCeiling ? length * width : 0
trimLinearFt = includeTrim ? 2 * (length + width) + (numDoors * 17) + (numWindows * 12) : 0

// Paint coverage (sq ft per gallon)
coveragePerGallon = 350  // standard estimate
gallonsNeeded = (paintableWallArea * numCoats) / coveragePerGallon

// Pricing by quality
pricePerGallon = { economy: 25, standard: 45, premium: 75 }
paintCost = gallonsNeeded * pricePerGallon[quality]

// Primer (if needed)
primerGallons = paintableWallArea / 400
primerCost = primerGallons * 30
```

**Outputs:**
- Gallons of paint needed (rounded up)
- Estimated paint cost
- Primer recommendation
- Paintable square footage
- Time estimate (based on ~100 sqft/hour)
- Materials checklist (tape, brushes, rollers, drop cloths)

**CTA:** "Generate complete painting estimates in seconds with C-Money AI →"

